Dataset: Blue carbon dynamics in seagrass and salt marshes: spatio-temporal variability and total carbon stocks

Authors: Tiaan Engelbrecht, Sophie von der Heyden, Andrew Ndhlovu <andhlovu@sun.ac.za>

Any use of this dataset must include a citation. The DOI: 10.25573/serc.29564621

The data release contains biomass and soil carbon profiles from tidal wetlands. The data itself is housed in separate .csv files which can by joined by relational attributes (ex. site_id and core_id).

Engelbrecht_et_al_2025_olifants_methods.csv - Contains methodological information on the soil core collection and processing.
Engelbrecht_et_al_2025_olifants_sites.csv - Contains information on sampling sites.
Engelbrecht_et_al_2025_olifants_cores.csv - Contains information on all individual soil cores associated with dataset.
Engelbrecht_et_al_2025_olifants_depthseries.csv - Contains raw depth-series information for all soil cores.
Engelbrecht_et_al_2025_olifants_species.csv - Contains taxonomic information associated with all soil cores. 

metadata.xml - Contains a full suite of descriptive metadata with all attribute and variables defined, units clarified, and geographic, temporal, and taxonomic coverages described according to Ecological Metadata Language Standards.

metadata.html - Is a simplified, visual and interactive version of metadata.xml for display purposes.